race.comment: THE HAMO (1) races forward. Won this grade at Ipswich first-up and the fronted up there again in tougher than this and was narrowly beaten. Will have taken further fitness and can bounce back. VIALE (6) showed good early speed and raced on the pace before fading beaten 2 lengths over 1200m at Doomben. Draws handy and is well placed to feature. HEADLINE LEGEND (11) settled too far back from a wide barrier at Ipswich over longer but just missed this trip at Toowoomba prior. That would have him in the money. SIR MAURICE (3) resumed at the Sunshine Coast in good order and will be sharper today. has the inside gate and his best numbers stack up. MERCHANT LADY (2) resumes and has won 3/4 fresh. Has the ability and the betting will be key.
